# Lamplight Design System — Cursor Rules

You are building the **Lamplight Design System** on Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind v4, and Radix UI.
The source of truth for all visual decisions is the Figma file. All tokens are emitted by Style Dictionary into `tokens/css/` and consumed via CSS custom properties.

---

## 1. Token Architecture — understand this before touching anything visual

The system has three layers. Only the bottom layer is consumed by components and app code.

```
Brand (primitives)  →  Alias (semantic names)  →  Mapped (component-facing, light + dark)
 --brand-scale-400       --alias-spacing-lg          --color-surface-action
 --brand-brand-600       --alias-border-radius-md     --color-text-body
                                                      --color-border-focus
```

**Rule: components and app pages reference only Mapped tokens and Alias spacing/radius tokens.
Never reference Brand tokens directly in component code.**

```tsx
// ✅ Correct — Mapped token
className="bg-[var(--color-surface-action)] text-[color:var(--color-text-on-action)]"

// ❌ Wrong — Brand token referenced directly
className="bg-[var(--brand-brand-600)]"

// ❌ Wrong — hardcoded value
className="bg-[#ac4e2c]"
style={{ backgroundColor: '#ac4e2c' }}
```

---

## 2. No inline styles — ever

`style={{}}` props are **banned** for anything a token or Tailwind utility can express.
The only legitimate uses of `style` are: dynamic numeric values that cannot be known at build time (e.g. a progress bar width from state, a canvas transform), or third-party animation libraries that require it.

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<div className="bg-[var(--color-surface-raised)] p-[var(--spacing-lg)]" />

// ❌ Wrong — every one of these has a token equivalent
<div style={{ backgroundColor: 'var(--color-surface-raised)' }} />
<div style={{ padding: '16px' }} />
<div style={{ color: '#383838' }} />
<div style={{ borderRadius: '4px' }} />
<div style={{ fontFamily: 'Open Sans' }} />
<div style={{ zIndex: 400 }} />
```

---

## 3. Colour — always use semantic Mapped tokens

Never use hex, rgb, or hsl values. Never use Tailwind's built-in colour palette (blue-500, gray-200, etc.) — those bypass the token system and break dark mode.

### Full token reference

**Text**
```
--color-text-headings        heading text
--color-text-body            primary body copy
--color-text-body-secondary  secondary / helper text
--color-text-action          links, interactive text
--color-text-action-hover    hovered links
--color-text-action-active   pressed links
--color-text-on-action       text on filled action surfaces (buttons)
--color-text-inverse         text on inverted surfaces (tooltips)
--color-text-disabled        disabled labels
--color-text-error           error messages
--color-text-success         success messages
--color-text-warning         warning messages
--color-text-information     info messages
```

**Icons**
```
--color-icon-default         default icon fill
--color-icon-action          interactive icon
--color-icon-action-hover
--color-icon-action-active
--color-icon-on-action       icon on filled button
--color-icon-disabled
--color-icon-error
--color-icon-success
--color-icon-warning
--color-icon-information
```

**Surfaces**
```
--color-surface-page         page background (outermost)
--color-surface-default      card / panel background
--color-surface-raised       elevated cards (pair with Elevation/Raised shadow)
--color-surface-overlay      dropdowns, modals, popovers
--color-surface-sunken       wells, input backgrounds, code blocks
--color-surface-action       filled button / primary action background
--color-surface-action-hover
--color-surface-action-active
--color-surface-disabled     disabled element fill
--color-surface-error        error state fill
--color-surface-success
--color-surface-warning
--color-surface-information
```

**Borders**
```
--color-border-default       default dividers
--color-border-bold          high-emphasis borders (selected rows, table headers)
--color-border-action        interactive element border
--color-border-action-hover
--color-border-action-active
--color-border-focus         focus ring colour
--color-border-disabled
--color-border-error
--color-border-success
--color-border-warning
--color-border-information
```

**Tailwind v4 utility syntax for colours:**
```tsx
// Backgrounds
"bg-[var(--color-surface-action)]"

// Text — always use color: prefix to force correct CSS property
"text-[color:var(--color-text-body)]"

// Borders
"border border-[color:var(--color-border-default)]"

// Fill (SVG)
"fill-[var(--color-icon-action)]"

// With opacity modifier
"bg-[var(--color-surface-action-hover)]/10"
```

