## 4. Spacing — use Alias spacing tokens, never arbitrary px

```
--spacing-xs   = 4px   tight internal padding
--spacing-sm   = 8px   compact padding, icon gaps
--spacing-md   = 12px  default component padding
--spacing-lg   = 16px  gaps between elements
--spacing-xl   = 24px  section-internal spacing
--spacing-2xl  = 32px  between sections
--spacing-3xl  = 48px  page-level spacing
```

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
"px-[var(--spacing-xl)] py-[var(--spacing-lg)]"
"gap-[var(--spacing-sm)]"
"mt-[var(--spacing-2xl)]"

// ❌ Wrong
"px-6"        // arbitrary Tailwind step — not a Lamplight token
"p-4"         // same
"gap-2"       // same
"mt-8"        // same
style={{ padding: '24px' }}
```

---

## 5. Border radius — use Alias radius tokens

```
--border-radius-none  = 0
--border-radius-sm    = 2px
--border-radius-md    = 4px   inputs, cards
--border-radius-lg    = 8px   modals, larger panels
--border-radius-xl    = 16px  feature cards
--border-radius-full  = 999px pill / fully rounded (buttons, badges)
```

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
"rounded-[var(--border-radius-md)]"
"rounded-[var(--border-radius-full)]"

// ❌ Wrong
"rounded"
"rounded-lg"
"rounded-full"
style={{ borderRadius: '4px' }}
```

---

## 6. Typography — use font and type scale tokens

```
--font-heading   = Merriweather  (h1–h6)
--font-body      = Open Sans     (body, UI labels, inputs)
--font-mono      = JetBrains Mono (code, badges, numeric data)

--type-h1-size / --type-h1-lh    (responsive via CSS vars)
--type-h2-size / --type-h2-lh
...
--type-paragraph-sm-size = 14px
--type-paragraph-md-size = 16px
--type-paragraph-xsm-size = 12px
```

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
"font-[family-name:var(--font-body)] text-[length:var(--type-paragraph-sm-size)]"
"font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)]"
"font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-[12px]"

// ❌ Wrong
"font-sans"
"font-serif"
"text-sm"          // uses Tailwind's scale, not Lamplight's
"text-base"
style={{ fontFamily: 'Open Sans' }}
style={{ fontSize: '14px' }}
```

---

## 7. Z-index — use Brand z-index tokens

```
--brand-z-index-base      = 0
--brand-z-index-dropdown  = 100
--brand-z-index-sticky    = 200
--brand-z-index-overlay   = 300  (modal backdrop)
--brand-z-index-modal     = 400
--brand-z-index-popover   = 500
--brand-z-index-toast     = 600
```

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
"z-[var(--brand-z-index-modal)]"
"z-[var(--brand-z-index-toast)]"

// ❌ Wrong
"z-50"
"z-[9999]"
style={{ zIndex: 400 }}
```

---

## 8. Elevation (shadows) — use effect styles

Use the four Figma effect styles as named CSS shadow utilities. Add to `globals.css` under `@layer utilities` if not yet present:

```css
@layer utilities {
  .shadow-raised  { box-shadow: 0 1px 2px  rgba(12,12,13,0.10); }
  .shadow-overlay { box-shadow: 0 2px 8px  rgba(12,12,13,0.12), 0 0 1px 1px rgba(12,12,13,0.06); }
  .shadow-modal   { box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(12,12,13,0.16); }
  .shadow-toast   { box-shadow: 0 16px 32px rgba(12,12,13,0.20); }
}
```

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
<div className="bg-[var(--color-surface-raised)] shadow-raised rounded-[var(--border-radius-lg)]" />
<div className="bg-[var(--color-surface-overlay)] shadow-overlay" />

// ❌ Wrong
style={{ boxShadow: '0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,0.1)' }}
"shadow-md"
"shadow-lg"
```

---

## 9. Focus rings — use the Focus Ring tokens

All interactive elements must have a visible focus ring using `Border/focus`. Never remove focus rings — only replace `:focus` with `:focus-visible`.

```
--focus-ring-width  = 2px
--focus-ring-offset = 2px
--color-border-focus
```

**For Radix-based components (Button, Checkbox, etc.):** the focus ring is an absolute `<span>` child shown via `group-focus-visible:opacity-100`. Follow the Button pattern.

**For native inputs:** use `focus-visible:ring` utilities:
```tsx
"outline-none focus-visible:ring-[length:var(--focus-ring-width)] focus-visible:ring-offset-[length:var(--focus-ring-offset)] focus-visible:ring-[var(--color-border-focus)]"
```

---

## 10. Dark mode — never hardcode for a theme

Dark mode is handled by `[data-theme="dark"]` on `<html>`, set by `next-themes`. Mapped tokens switch automatically — **never** write `dark:` Tailwind variants for colour; they fight the token layer.

```tsx
// ✅ Correct — token switches automatically
<div className="bg-[var(--color-surface-default)] text-[color:var(--color-text-body)]" />

// ❌ Wrong — bypasses the token system
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100" />
```

The only valid use of `dark:` is for non-colour structural adjustments (e.g. `dark:shadow-none` if a shadow needs to disappear in dark mode and there's no token for it yet — add the token instead if possible).

---

## 11. Component usage — always reach for @lamplight/ui first

Before writing any UI, check if `@lamplight/ui` exports it.

```tsx
import {
  Button, IconWrapper, Badge,
  Input, InputLabel, InputCaption,
  Checkbox, IndeterminateCheckbox,
  Divider,
  cn,
} from '@lamplight/ui';
```

**Never reimplement a component that already exists.** If a variant is missing, extend the existing component — don't create a parallel one.

### Component patterns

```tsx
// Button — always use variant + size props, never restyle with className colours
<Button variant="fill" size="md">Save changes</Button>
<Button variant="outline" size="sm" leadingIcon={<Search size={16} />}>Search</Button>
<Button variant="ghost" disabled>Cancel</Button>

// Button as Next.js Link
<Button asChild variant="fill">
  <Link href="/dashboard">Go to dashboard</Link>
</Button>

// Badge — sentiment + contrast + showText axes
<Badge sentiment="negative" contrast="high">3</Badge>
<Badge sentiment="positive" contrast="default">Active</Badge>
<Badge sentiment="warning" showText={false} />  {/* dot */}

// Input — always use the composite component
<Input
  label="Email"
  required
  hint="Optional"
  placeholder="you@example.com"
  caption="We'll never share this."
  captionType="info"
/>

// Input with error state — captionType="error" turns the border red
<Input
  label="Password"
  type="password"
  caption="Must be at least 8 characters"
  captionType="error"
/>

// Checkbox with indeterminate (select-all pattern)
<IndeterminateCheckbox
  checked={allChecked ? true : noneChecked ? false : 'indeterminate'}
  onCheckedChange={handleSelectAll}
/>

// IconWrapper — always pass size, never set width/height manually on the icon
<IconWrapper icon={<Search />} size="sm" className="text-[color:var(--color-icon-action)]" />

// Divider — horizontal/vertical/labelled
<Divider orientation="horizontal" />
<Divider orientation="vertical" />
<Divider label="or" />
```

