## 16. File and folder conventions

```
packages/ui/src/components/
  ComponentName/
    ComponentName.tsx      ← component + exported types
    ComponentName.stories.tsx ← Storybook stories (all variants)
    index.ts               ← re-export (optional, for cleaner imports)

apps/web/src/
  app/                     ← Next.js App Router pages
    (group)/
      page.tsx
      layout.tsx
  components/              ← app-specific, non-library components
  hooks/                   ← custom hooks
  lib/                     ← utilities
```

New components that are design-system primitives → `packages/ui`.
Page-specific, one-off components → `apps/web/src/components`.

---

## 17. What to do when a token doesn't exist yet

If you need a value that has no token:
1. Check `tokens/css/mapped.light.css` — it may exist under a different name.
2. Check `tokens/css/alias.css` for spacing/radius/elevation values.
3. If it truly doesn't exist, add it to Figma first, re-export tokens, run `npm run tokens`.
4. **Never** hardcode the value as a stopgap.

Common mistakes:
```tsx
// ❌ "I need 20px padding and there's no spacing token for it"
"p-5"  or  style={{ padding: '20px' }}
// ✅ Use the nearest token (xl=24 or lg=16) and flag the gap for design review

// ❌ "I need a gray that's between two tokens"
"text-[#9ca3af]"
// ✅ Use the nearest semantic token and flag
```

